line_1: Substance, or Accident divides

line_1: AVARO from the Stern the Boat divides,
line_2: And yields up to the Fury of the Tides:

line_1: Drives back the Blood, and all the Mass divides.

line_1: Euphrates in its course the town divides,
line_2: While thro' the midst his stately current glides.

line_1: The plenteous stream in various rills divides,
line_2: While marble bounds confine the crystal tides.

line_1: Her chariot set with pearl, the wave divides,
line_2: Softly along the silver stream she glides.

line_1: No refluent fin the unpeopled stream divides,

line_1: Such is that room which one rude beam divides,
line_2: And naked rafters form the sloping sides;

line_1: An interest dear their heart divides;

line_1: With wat'ry Parts it's lessen'd Force divides;

line_1: By this she now compares things, now divides;

line_1: To each our Task he readily divides,

line_1: Still as he turns, the troubl'd Sea divides;
line_2: And rolls in Eddies from his slimy Sides.

line_1: The crooked Keel the frothy Flood divides,
line_2: Swift flies the Ship, and rushes thro' the Tides.
